Notes.Text:
This update for libxml2 fixes the following issues:

  - CVE-2022-40303: Fixed integer overflows with XML_PARSE_HUGE (bsc#1204366).
  - CVE-2022-40304: Fixed dict corruption caused by entity reference cycles (bsc#1204367).

Vulnerabilities.Description: An issue was discovered in libxml2 before 2.10.3. When parsing a multi-gigabyte XML document with the XML_PARSE_HUGE parser option enabled, several integer counters can overflow. This results in an attempt to access an array at a negative 2GB offset, typically leading to a segmentation fault.

Vulnerabilities.Description: An issue was discovered in libxml2 before 2.10.3. Certain invalid XML entity definitions can corrupt a hash table key, potentially leading to subsequent logic errors. In one case, a double-free can be provoked.
